    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix M3AP timer checking functionality\n\n### Summary\nThe `m3ap_check_timers()` function in `m3ap_timers.c` was mostly commented out and not functioning properly. This caused M3AP handover timers to not be checked, leading to potential stuck handover processes and resource leaks.\n\nThis fix implements the timer checking logic based on the X2AP implementation pattern.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/M3AP/m3ap_timers.c`: Uncommented and properly implemented the `m3ap_check_timers()` function\n- `openair2/COMMON/m3ap_messages_types.h`: Added handover cancel cause definitions and message structure\n\n### Reproduction\nWithout this fix, calling `m3ap_check_timers()` does not perform any timer checking. Handover processes that exceed their timeout values (t_reloc_prep or tm3_reloc_overall) will not be properly cancelled, leading to stuck UE contexts in the M3AP layer. This can be observed by:\n1. Initiating an M3AP handover process\n2. Letting the handover exceed its configured timeout values\n3. Noticing that no timeout handling occurs and the UE context remains allocated\n\nThe fix ensures that timeout conditions are properly detected and appropriate cancellation messages are sent to the RRC layer.\n"
}